---
description: Require Conventional Commit message output after settled code changes
globs: ["**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

When code changes were made and the task is complete:
- Always include a suggested Conventional Commit message in the final response.
- Follow the format from `.cursor/rules/commits.mdc`: `type(scope): description`.
- If no code changes were made, do not include a commit message.
- Do not run `git commit` unless the user explicitly asks.

Before suggesting a commit message, follow `.cursor/rules/workflow.mdc` verification requirements.
